info.title: PlayFab CloudScript API
info.description: API methods for executing CloudScript using an Entity Profile

post.description: Cloud Script is one of PlayFab's most versatile features. It allows client code to request execution of any kind of custom server-side functionality you can implement, and it can be used in conjunction with virtually anything.
post.x-requestDetails: Executes CloudScript with the entity profile that is defined in the request.

ApiErrorWrapper.description: The basic wrapper around every failed API response

errorDetails.description: Detailed description of individual issues with the request object

Name.description: The name of the email info data

VerificationStatus.description: The verification status of the email

EntityKey.description: Combined entity type and ID structure which uniquely identifies a single entity.

APIRequestsIssued.description: Number of PlayFab API requests issued by the CloudScript function

Error.description: Information about the error, if any, that occurred during execution

FunctionName.description: The name of the function that executed

FunctionResult.description: The object returned from the CloudScript function, if any

FunctionResultTooLarge.description: Flag indicating if the FunctionResult was too large and was subsequently dropped from this event. This only occurs if the total event size is larger than 350KB.

HttpRequestsIssued.description: Number of external HTTP requests issued by the CloudScript function

Logs.description: Entries logged during the function execution. These include both entries logged in the function code using log.info() and log.error() and error entries for API and HTTP request failures.

LogsTooLarge.description: Flag indicating if the logs were too large and were subsequently dropped from this event. This only occurs if the total event size is larger than 350KB after the FunctionResult was removed.

ProcessorTimeSeconds.description: Processor time consumed while executing the function. This does not include time spent waiting on API calls or HTTP requests.

Revision.description: The revision of the CloudScript that executed

ExecuteEntityCloudScriptRequest.description: Executes CloudScript with the entity profile that is defined in the request.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The entity to perform this action on.

FunctionName.description: The name of the CloudScript function to execute

FunctionParameter.description: Object that is passed in to the function as the first argument

GeneratePlayStreamEvent.description: Generate a 'entity_executed_cloudscript' PlayStream event containing the results of the function execution and other contextual information. This event will show up in the PlayStream debugger console for the player in Game Manager.

RevisionSelection.description: Option for which revision of the CloudScript to execute. 'Latest' executes the most recently created revision, 'Live' executes the current live, published revision, and 'Specific' executes the specified revision. The default value is 'Specific', if the SpecificRevision parameter is specified, otherwise it is 'Live'.

SpecificRevision.description: The specific revision to execute, when RevisionSelection is set to 'Specific'

ExecuteFunctionRequest.description: Executes an Azure Function with the profile of the entity that is defined in the request.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Entity.description: The entity to perform this action on.

FunctionName.description: The name of the CloudScript function to execute

FunctionParameter.description: Object that is passed in to the function as the FunctionArgument field of the FunctionExecutionContext data structure

GeneratePlayStreamEvent.description: Generate a 'entity_executed_cloudscript_function' PlayStream event containing the results of the function execution and other contextual information. This event will show up in the PlayStream debugger console for the player in Game Manager.

Error.description: Error from the CloudScript Azure Function.

ExecutionTimeMilliseconds.description: The amount of time the function took to execute

FunctionName.description: The name of the function that executed

FunctionResult.description: The object returned from the function, if any

FunctionResultTooLarge.description: Flag indicating if the FunctionResult was too large and was subsequently dropped from this event.

Error.description: Error code, such as CloudScriptAzureFunctionsExecutionTimeLimitExceeded, CloudScriptAzureFunctionsArgumentSizeExceeded, CloudScriptAzureFunctionsReturnSizeExceeded or CloudScriptAzureFunctionsHTTPRequestError

StackTrace.description: Point during the execution of the function at which the error occurred, if any

FunctionName.description: The name the function was registered under.

TriggerType.description: The trigger type for the function.

FunctionName.description: The name the function was registered under.

Email.description: Linked account email of the user on the platform, if available

PlatformUserId.description: Unique account identifier of the user on the platform

Username.description: Linked account username of the user on the platform, if available

ListFunctionsRequest.description: A title can have many functions, ListHttpFunctions will return a list of all the currently registered HTTP triggered functions for a given title.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

Functions.description: The list of functions that are currently registered for the title.
The list of HTTP triggered functions that are currently registered for the title.
The list of Queue triggered functions that are currently registered for the title.

ContinentCode.description: The two-character continent code for this location

CountryCode.description: The two-character ISO 3166-1 country code for the country associated with the location

Latitude.description: Latitude coordinate of the geographic location.

Longitude.description: Longitude coordinate of the geographic location.

Data.description: Optional object accompanying the message as contextual information

IsActive.description: Whether this membership is active. That is, whether the MembershipExpiration time has been reached.

OverrideExpiration.description: Membership expirations can be explicitly overridden (via game manager or the admin api). If this membership has been overridden, this will be the new expiration time.

OverrideIsSet.description: Whether the override expiration is set.

Subscriptions.description: The list of subscriptions that this player has for this membership

NameIdentifier.description: Identifier by either name or ID. Note that a name may change due to renaming, or reused after being deleted. ID is immutable and unique.

AdCampaignAttributions.description: List of advertising campaigns the player has been attributed to

AvatarUrl.description: URL of the player's avatar image

BannedUntil.description: If the player is currently banned, the UTC Date when the ban expires

ContactEmailAddresses.description: List of all contact email info associated with the player account

ExperimentVariants.description: List of experiment variants for the player.

LastLogin.description: UTC time when the player most recently logged in to the title

LinkedAccounts.description: List of all authentication systems linked to this player account

Locations.description: List of geographic locations from which the player has logged in to the title

Memberships.description: List of memberships for the player, along with whether are expired.

PushNotificationRegistrations.description: List of configured end points registered for sending the player push notifications

Statistics.description: List of leaderboard statistic values for the player

Tags.description: List of player's tags for segmentation

TitleId.description: Title ID this player profile applies to

TotalValueToDateInUSD.description: Sum of the player's purchases made with real-money currencies, converted to US dollars equivalent and represented as a whole number of cents (1/100 USD). For example, 999 indicates nine dollars and ninety-nine cents.

ValuesToDate.description: List of the player's lifetime purchase totals, summed by real-money currency

FunctionResult.description: The result of the function execution

FunctionName.description: The name the function was registered under.

FunctionUrl.description: Full URL for Azure Function that implements the function.

RegisterQueuedFunctionRequest.description: A title can have many functions, RegisterQueuedFunction associates a function name with a queue name and connection string.

ConnectionString.description: A connection string for the storage account that hosts the queue for the Azure Function.

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

FunctionName.description: The name of the function to register

QueueName.description: The name of the queue for the Azure Function.

Error.description: Error code, such as CloudScriptNotFound, JavascriptException, CloudScriptFunctionArgumentSizeExceeded, CloudScriptAPIRequestCountExceeded, CloudScriptAPIRequestError, or CloudScriptHTTPRequestError

StackTrace.description: Point during the execution of the script at which the error occurred, if any

Version.description: Statistic version (0 if not a versioned statistic)

InitialSubscriptionTime.description: The time the subscription was orignially purchased

IsActive.description: Whether this subscription is currently active. That is, if Expiration > now.

Status.description: The status of this subscription, according to the subscription provider.

SubscriptionItemId.description: The item id for this subscription from the primary catalog

SubscriptionProvider.description: The provider for this subscription. Apple or Google Play are supported today.

TagValue.description: Full value of the tag, including namespace

CustomTags.description: The optional custom tags associated with the request (e.g. build number, external trace identifiers, etc.).

FunctionName.description: The name of the function to unregister

Currency.description: ISO 4217 code of the currency used in the purchases

TotalValue.description: Total value of the purchases in a whole number of 1/100 monetary units. For example, 999 indicates nine dollars and ninety-nine cents when Currency is 'USD')

TotalValueAsDecimal.description: Total value of the purchases in a string representation of decimal monetary units. For example, '9.99' indicates nine dollars and ninety-nine cents when Currency is 'USD'.
